Script,RabbisRule
window.currentPBSScenario = 'RabbisRule';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Rabbis_Rule';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for RabbisRule');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'RabbisRule',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1S
*/
# Predeal: south's solid trumps + diamond AQ + heart A; west's stiff K of
# diamonds; east's heart KQ threat.
predeal south SAKQ,HA,DAQ
predeal west  DK
predeal east  HKQ

dealer south

# ----- Declarer (South) — 1S opener with 5+ spade suit -----
sSpades   = spades(south) > 4
sHcp      = hcp(south) > 13 and hcp(south) < 18
sDiamonds = diamonds(south) > 3 and diamonds(south) < 6   # 4-5 diamonds with AQ
southHand = sSpades and sHcp and sDiamonds

# ----- Dummy (North) — game-raising response -----
nSpades   = spades(north) > 2 and spades(north) < 5
nHcp      = hcp(north) > 7 and hcp(north) < 12
nDiamonds = diamonds(north) > 1 and diamonds(north) < 5   # 2-4 (loose)
northHand = nSpades and nHcp and nDiamonds

# ----- West — STIFF K of diamonds -----
wDiamonds = diamonds(west) == 1           # K alone
wHcp      = hcp(west) < 11
westHand = wDiamonds and wHcp

# ----- East — long hearts headed by KQ -----
eHearts   = hearts(east) > 4
eHcp      = hcp(east) < 11
eastHand = eHearts and eHcp

southHand and northHand and westHand and eastHand

action printoneline,
average "West stiff K (forced)  " 100 * (diamonds(west) == 1),
average "East 5+ hearts (forced)" 100 * (hearts(east) > 4),
average "South HCP              "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP              "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Rabbi's Rule,\n\
--- Rabbi's Rule (4!S) — drop the singleton King\n\
"When the King is singleton，play the Ace." Here it's a safety play.\n\
\n\
South opens 1!S and the partnership reaches 4!S.\n\
\n\
Teaching feature: declarer holds AQxxx of diamonds opposite xxx in dummy.\n\
The King is missing. The natural impulse is to finesse — but West has the\n\
SINGLETON K. East has the rest of the diamonds (4 cards，Jxxx).\n\
\n\
• Play the Ace first: the stiff K drops，and the Queen is good. You make.\n\
• Finesse (lead from dummy，play Q): the Q loses to West's K. West can put\n\
  East in via a club，and East cashes the long heart suit. Down 2 or more.\n\
\n\
The key: Rabbi's Rule isn't "you gain a trick by laying down the A" — it's\n\
that the FINESSE costs the contract when the K is stiff and the opp can\n\
reach the long suit. Cashing the A is the safety play.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• Count your tricks before you commit to a line in diamonds.\n\
• What clues does the auction give about distribution?\n\
• If the auction is silent，the 4-1 split with K stiff offside is exactly\n\
  what makes Rabbi's Rule shine.\n\
%RabbisRule%
